                "url": "/topics/i_write"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522646",
        "quote": "Medicine, you see, is my first love; whether I write fiction or nonfiction, and even when it has nothing to do with medicine, it's still about medicine. After all, what is medicine but life plus? So I write about life.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522646"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Love",
                "url": "/topics/love"
            },
            {
                "name": "Still",
                "url": "/topics/still"
            },
            {
                "name": "I Write",
                "url": "/topics/i_write"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522649",
        "quote": "I was taking care of people my age who were dying. The constant feeling, hearing from them, was that life is transient and can end very quickly, so don't postpone your dreams.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522649"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Constant",
                "url": "/topics/constant"
            },
            {
                "name": "Quickly",
                "url": "/topics/quickly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522651",
        "quote": "My writing flows out of my doctorhood. They are not separate things. They are one. I think the foremost connection between being a doctor and being a writer is the great privilege of having an intimate view of one's fellow humans, the privilege of being there and helping other people at their most vulnerable moments.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522651"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "I Think",
                "url": "/topics/i_think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Separate",
                "url": "/topics/separate"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522652",
        "quote": "In writing, as in medicine, there are no short cuts. You need stamina.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522652"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Writing",
                "url": "/topics/writing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Need",
                "url": "/topics/need"
            },
            {
                "name": "Stamina",
                "url": "/topics/stamina"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522653",
        "quote": "There is that lovely feeling of one reader telling another, 'You must read this.' I've always wanted to write a book like that, with the sense that you are contributing to the discourse in middle America, a discourse that begins at a book club in a living room, but then spreads. That is meaningful to me.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522653"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Telling",
                "url": "/topics/telling"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reader",
                "url": "/topics/reader"
            },
            {
                "name": "Another",
                "url": "/topics/another"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522619",
        "quote": "Rituals, anthropologists will tell us, are about transformation. The rituals we use for marriage, baptism or inaugurating a president are as elaborate as they are because we associate the ritual with a major life passage, the crossing of a critical threshold, or in other words, with transformation.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522619"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Passage",
                "url": "/topics/passage"
            },
            {
                "name": "Elaborate",
                "url": "/topics/elaborate"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522648",
        "quote": "Students undergo a conversion in the third year of medical school - not pre-clinical to clinical, but pre-cynical to cynical.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522648"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Third",
                "url": "/topics/third"
            },
            {
                "name": "Clinical",
                "url": "/topics/clinical"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522637",
        "quote": "Literature is a beautiful way of keeping the imagination alive, of visiting worlds you would never have time to in your day-to-day life. It keeps you abreast of a wider spectrum of human activities.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522637"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Wider",
                "url": "/topics/wider"
            },
            {
                "name": "Day-To-Day Life",
                "url": "/topics/day-to-day_life"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522611",
        "quote": "I think we learn from medicine everywhere that it is, at its heart, a human endeavor, requiring good science but also a limitless curiosity and interest in your fellow human being, and that the physician-patient relationship is key; all else follows from it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522611"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Good",
                "url": "/topics/good"
            },
            {
                "name": "I Think",
                "url": "/topics/i_think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Your",
                "url": "/topics/your"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522642",
        "quote": "I joke, but only half joke, that if you show up in an American hospital missing a finger, no one will believe you until they get a CAT scan, MRI and orthopedic consult.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522642"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Half",
                "url": "/topics/half"
            },
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "Finger",
                "url": "/topics/finger"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522640",
        "quote": "My desire to be a physician had a lot to do with that sense of medicine as a ministry of healing, not just a science. And not even just a science and an art, but also a calling, also a ministry.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522640"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Art",
                "url": "/topics/art"
            },
            {
                "name": "Desire",
                "url": "/topics/desire"
            },
            {
                "name": "Had",
                "url": "/topics/had"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522613",
        "quote": "When you have a natural genetic tan developed over centuries and many generations, the idea of soaking up rays by the pool has never made sense.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522613"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Tan",
                "url": "/topics/tan"
            },
            {
                "name": "Genetic",
                "url": "/topics/genetic"
            },
            {
                "name": "Over",
                "url": "/topics/over"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522622",
        "quote": "What we need in medical schools is not to teach empathy, as much as to preserve it - the process of learning huge volumes of information about disease, of learning a specialized language, can ironically make one lose sight of the patient one came to serve; empathy can be replaced by cynicism.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522622"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Specialized",
                "url": "/topics/specialized"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522607",
        "quote": "I'm a great believer in geography being destiny.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522607"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Destiny",
                "url": "/topics/destiny"
            },
            {
                "name": "Geography",
                "url": "/topics/geography"
            },
            {
                "name": "Believer",
                "url": "/topics/believer"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522650",
        "quote": "I think America is really in denial about the degree to which residents, particularly foreign medical graduates, man the county hospitals of this country, and but for their services, I'm not sure how exactly we could manage.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522650"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Country",
                "url": "/topics/country"
