            {
                "name": "Hospitals",
                "url": "/topics/hospitals"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522623",
        "quote": "Though I am fascinated by knowledge, I am even more fascinated by wisdom.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522623"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "I Am",
                "url": "/topics/i_am"
            },
            {
                "name": "Even",
                "url": "/topics/even"
            },
            {
                "name": "Though",
                "url": "/topics/though"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522631",
        "quote": "Modern society has evolved to the point where we counter the old-fashioned fatalism surrounding the word 'cancer' by embracing the idea of the Uber-mind - that our will possesses nearly supernatural powers.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522631"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "Idea",
                "url": "/topics/idea"
            },
            {
                "name": "Surrounding",
                "url": "/topics/surrounding"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522647",
        "quote": "By visiting patients in their home, by helping them come to terms with their illness, I could heal when I could not cure.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522647"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Helping",
                "url": "/topics/helping"
            },
            {
                "name": "Visiting",
                "url": "/topics/visiting"
            },
            {
                "name": "Could",
                "url": "/topics/could"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522633",
        "quote": "My deceased patients have taught me over the years to believe in the glass half full, to make good use of the time we have, to be generous - that was their lesson for the Uber-mind, and it was free. 'Do that,' they said, 'and then perhaps death shall have no dominion.'",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522633"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Death",
                "url": "/topics/death"
            },
            {
                "name": "Half",
                "url": "/topics/half"
            },
            {
                "name": "Deceased",
                "url": "/topics/deceased"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522612",
        "quote": "I think we can see how blessed we are in America to have access to the kind of health care we do if we are insured, and even if uninsured, how there is a safety net. Now, as to the problem of how much health care costs and how we reform health care ... it is another story altogether.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Abraham Verghese",
            "url": "/quotes/abraham_verghese_522612"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "I Think",
